Its gold polyurethane and stainless steel bracelet-style band has a fold-over clasp to lock and hold the oversized gold-toned stainless steel case in place. The dial is white, and gold-toned numeric hour markers and luminous hands contrast while keeping the look light. With a durable mineral crystal, Japanese quartz movement, and water-resistance to 165 feet (50 meters), the Michael Kors can take a few knocks without missing a beat.

EditorialReview.Content: Sporty with a surprising casual look, the Michael Kors Chronograph Tortoise Watch has style to spare. Both its bracelet-style stainless-steel band and case are finished in brown for a rich, relaxed look that nicely side-steps the ruggedness of other chronographs. Gold-toned bezel, hour markers, function buttons, and hands provide a smart complement, while crystal chips on the hour markers add shine. Three chronographs track seconds, minutes, and 24-hour information. A date window sits at the four o'clock position. A durable mineral crystal, Japanese quartz movement, and water-resistance to 330 feet (100 meters) mean the Michel Kors can take a knock without skipping a beat. The band's deployment-style clasp keeps it securely in place.

EditorialReview.Content: The White Runway Watch by Michael Kors Women's couples a little glitz with functionality. This watch has a polished stainless steel case and white band with a deployment clasp. It has an eye-catching mother-of-pearl dial and bezel that are adorned with crystals that glisten like diamonds. This watch features silver-toned hour sticks and delicate silver-toned hands that move with quartz movement. Three chronographs track minutes, seconds, and hours on a 24-hour clock, and a small window at the four o'clock position provides the date. Water-resistance to 165 feet (50 meters), a durable mineral crystal, and quartz movement mean this watch can handle wear and tear.
